params.unstakeDelaySec: Duration (in seconds) after which the stake can be unlocked

constructor.details: Initializes the factory with the wallet implementation and entry point addresses

createWallet(bytes,bytes32).details: Deploys the SoulWallet using a proxy and returns the proxy's address

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxyCode().details: Used by soulwalletlib to calculate the SoulWallet address

returns._0: Byte array representing the proxy's creation code

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.withdrawAddress: Address to receive the withdrawn stake
Address to receive the withdrawn ETH

addStake(uint32).notice: Allows the owner to add stake to the entry point

deposit().notice: Deposits ETH to the entry point on behalf of the contract

getWalletAddress(bytes,bytes32).notice: Calculates the counterfactual address of the SoulWallet as it would be returned by `createWallet`

unlockStake().notice: Allows the owner to unlock their stake from the entry point

withdrawStake(address).notice: Allows the owner to withdraw their stake from the entry point

withdrawTo(address,uint256).notice: Allows the owner to withdraw ETH from entrypoint contract
